"label": "R25: Federico Barocci, <i>Virgin and Child with Saint John</i>, before 1575–6, black charcoal on white paper, (12 x 11.7 cm), (inv. 11463 F recto, Gabinetto dei Disegni e delle Stampe, Galleria degli Uffizi, Florence) <br/>In this very early sketch for the main group of figures in ‘The Madonna of the Cat (‘La Madonna del Gatto’)’, Barocci represents the Virgin holding the Christ Child on her lap and embracing Saint John the Baptist with her right arm. The idea of depicting the interaction between the two children had proved very successful during the Renaissance and Barocci may have had examples by Raphael and other masters in mind whilst executing this early sketch. <br/>© By courtesy of the Ministero per i Beni e le Attività Culturali\nFile:R-0025-00-000002-PYR.tif (3050x2943px)",
