"label": "R26: Federico Barocci, <i>Virgin and Child with Saint John</i>, before 1575–6, black chalk and pen and ink with white heightening on white paper, (15.5 x 11 cm), (inv. 11542 F recto, Gabinetto dei Disegni e delle Stampe, Galleria degli Uffizi, Florence) <br/>This sheet, which has been cut down from its original size, shows a composition closely related to another drawing from the Gabinetto dei Disegni e delle Stampe degli Uffizi, Florence (R24). In both studies the two children are about to kiss each other. However, in this drawing, which is in worse condition, Barocci uses the technique of white heightening to depict the light effects used in the mother and child group. It is clear that Barocci had already decided at this stage that the light source for his painting should be placed to the left of the composition. <br/>© By courtesy of the Ministero per i Beni e le Attività Culturali\nFile:R-0026-00-000002-PYR.tif (3687x2648px)",
