"label": "R56: Federico Barocci, <i>Sketch for the Virgin and Child with Saint John</i>, before 1575–6, black chalk, pen and ink with wash on white paper, (30.3 x 23.4 cm), (inv. 11477 F recto, Gabinetto dei Disegni e delle Stampe degli Uffizi, Florence) <br/>This sheet records Barocci’s rapid initial trials for the group of the Virgin and two children in ‘The Madonna of the Cat (‘La Madonna del Gatto’). He began experimenting in black chalk, but then inverted the sheet to continue a new series of drawings in pen and wash. His main concerns were the distribution of light and shadow, and the young John the Baptist’s dynamic diagonal pose. Barocci’s sensitive use of wash highlights key passages such as the Virgin’s bare breast and the children’s joyful expressions. <br/>© Photo Scala, Florence - courtesy of the Ministero per i Beni e le Attività Culturali\nFile:R-0056-00-000002-PYR.tif (3207x2539px)",
